-- Acciona Agua Awarded Saudi Wastewater Plant Contracts in Mecca
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-01-21T12:39:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-21/acciona-agua-awarded-saudi-wastewater-plant-contracts-in-mecca.html
Acciona SA (ANA) , which has built more
than 70 desalination plants globally, said a subsidiary won a
two-year operating and maintenance contract from  Saudi Arabia ’s
state water utility for wastewater treatment plants between
Jeddah and Mecca.  The wastewater treatment facilities’ combined daily
capacity of 375,000 cubic meters is meant to serve the cities of
Haddah and Arana, Alcobendas, Spain-based Acciona said in a web
statement announcing that it and the Miahona joint venture were
awarded the 14 million-euro ($19 million) contract.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
